1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Meet MnemoGuard, a zero-trust memory firewall for autonomous AI agents.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:13,000
In the next two and a half minutes, we will poison an agent's memory, compare outcomes, and inspect the evidence.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:19,000
The live dashboard is running on AWS Lambda and connected to CockroachDB Cloud.

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:24,000
It shows three durable memories: one trusted record and two quarantined records.

5
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:31,000
MnemoGuard evaluates memory before it can enter an agent's context or trigger a real-world action.

6
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Here is the attack.

7
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:43,000
A compromised support chat injects a new refund limit of ten thousand dollars, marks the customer V I P, and removes approval requirements.

8
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Before execution, both agents receive exactly the same retrieved claim.

9
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:54,000
The baseline agent trusts the newest memory and approves a ten-thousand-dollar refund.

10
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:58,000
MnemoGuard blocks it and requires human review.

11
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,000
The result is not a prompt suggestion.

12
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:07,000
The poisoned record remains auditable, but it cannot cross the trusted-memory boundary or reach the agent.

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:17,000
The policy score reaches one hundred because the source is untrusted, unsigned, high impact, and contradicts the signed C R M record.

14
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:22,000
AWS Lambda runs this intake pipeline independently of the agent.

15
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:32,000
The guard writes its decision to CockroachDB, while the read-only CockroachDB Managed M C P Server exposes only the trusted view for agent recall.

16
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,000
CockroachDB is the durable memory system of record.

17
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Trusted and quarantined assertions remain transactionally consistent with their embeddings.

18
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Distributed Vector Indexing retrieves related memories for contradiction checks, while append-only decision events preserve the audit trail.

19
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Here we can see the trusted five-hundred-dollar limit beside the quarantined poison.

20
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
The complete implementation is open source.

21
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:16,000
The repository includes the trust engine, H T T P API, CockroachDB schema, Lambda handlers, public demo hardening, automated tests, deployment scripts, and a reproducible fallback path.

22
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Twelve validation tests pass.

23
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:27,000
The architecture uses both required CockroachDB capabilities: Distributed Vector Indexing and the Cloud Managed M C P Server.

24
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:30,000
AWS Lambda provides serverless execution.

25
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:41,000
A constrained Amazon Bedrock adjudicator handles ambiguous cases when inference quota is available, but deterministic policy always remains authoritative.

26
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:48,000
MnemoGuard turns persistent agent memory from an implicit risk into an enforceable security boundary.

27
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Try the live demo, inspect the audit evidence, and review the source code from the Devpost submission.

28
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Thank you.

